<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>emsenn.net</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/</link><description>Recent content on emsenn.net</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Basis</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/basis/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/basis/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A basis of a &lt;a href="./vector-space.md" class="link-internal"&gt;vector space&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;V&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a linearly independent set of &lt;a href="./vector.md" class="link-internal"&gt;vectors&lt;/a&gt; that spans &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;V&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. Every vector in &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;V&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; can be written uniquely as a linear combination of basis vectors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every vector space has a basis (this requires the axiom of choice for infinite-dimensional spaces). All bases of a given vector space have the same cardinality, called the &lt;a href="./dimension.md" class="link-internal"&gt;dimension&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;V&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The choice of basis determines the &lt;a href="./matrix.md" class="link-internal"&gt;matrix&lt;/a&gt; representation of &lt;a href="./linear-map.md" class="link-internal"&gt;linear maps&lt;/a&gt;. Changing the basis changes the matrix but not the underlying map.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Determinant</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/determinant/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/determinant/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The determinant is a &lt;a href="../../../concepts/function/index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;function&lt;/a&gt; from square &lt;a href="./matrix.md" class="link-internal"&gt;matrices&lt;/a&gt; to the underlying &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/field.md" class="link-internal"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt;. It is the unique alternating multilinear function of the columns that sends the identity matrix to &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;1&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The determinant encodes invertibility: a matrix &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;A&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is invertible if and only if &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;det&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal"&gt;≠&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\det(A) \neq 0&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. It is multiplicative: &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;det&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;det&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;det&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\det(AB) = \det(A)\det(B)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. Geometrically, &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;∣&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;det&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;∣&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;|\det(A)|&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; measures the factor by which the &lt;a href="./linear-map.md" class="link-internal"&gt;linear map&lt;/a&gt; scales volumes, and the sign records whether orientation is preserved or reversed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For a &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;2&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;×&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;2&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;2 \times 2&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; matrix &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo fence="true"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mtable rowspacing="0.16em" columnalign="center center" columnspacing="1em"&gt;&lt;mtr&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mstyle&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mstyle&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;/mtr&gt;&lt;mtr&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mstyle&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;mtd&gt;&lt;mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mstyle&gt;&lt;/mtd&gt;&lt;/mtr&gt;&lt;/mtable&gt;&lt;mo fence="true"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\begin{pmatrix} a &amp;amp; b \\ c &amp;amp; d \end{pmatrix}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the determinant is &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;−&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;ad - bc&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Dimension</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/dimension/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/dimension/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The dimension of a &lt;a href="./vector-space.md" class="link-internal"&gt;vector space&lt;/a&gt; is the number of elements in any &lt;a href="./basis.md" class="link-internal"&gt;basis&lt;/a&gt;. This is well-defined because all bases have the same cardinality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Two finite-dimensional vector spaces over the same &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/field.md" class="link-internal"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt; are isomorphic if and only if they have the same dimension. Dimension is therefore the complete invariant for finite-dimensional vector spaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="double-struck"&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\mathbb{R}^n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; has dimension &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. The space of polynomials of degree at most &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;d&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; has dimension &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;d + 1&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Eigenvalue</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/eigenvalue/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/eigenvalue/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;An eigenvalue of a &lt;a href="./linear-map.md" class="link-internal"&gt;linear map&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T : V \to V&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a scalar &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;λ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\lambda&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; such that &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;λ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T(\mathbf{v}) = \lambda \mathbf{v}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; for some nonzero &lt;a href="./vector.md" class="link-internal"&gt;vector&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\mathbf{v}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, called an eigenvector corresponding to &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;λ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\lambda&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eigenvalues are the roots of the characteristic &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/polynomial.md" class="link-internal"&gt;polynomial&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;det&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;−&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;λ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;I&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\det(A - \lambda I) = 0&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. A linear map on a finite-dimensional space has at most &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; eigenvalues (counted with multiplicity), where &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the &lt;a href="./dimension.md" class="link-internal"&gt;dimension&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eigenvalues reveal the &amp;ldquo;natural scales&amp;rdquo; of a linear map: the directions along which the map acts by pure stretching or compression, without rotation.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Linear Map</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/linear-map/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/linear-map/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A linear map &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;W&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T : V \to W&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a &lt;a href="../../../concepts/function/index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;function&lt;/a&gt; between &lt;a href="./vector-space.md" class="link-internal"&gt;vector spaces&lt;/a&gt; over the same &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/field.md" class="link-internal"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt; that preserves addition and scalar multiplication: &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;u&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;u&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T(\mathbf{u} + \mathbf{v}) = T(\mathbf{u}) + T(\mathbf{v})&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;T(a\mathbf{v}) = aT(\mathbf{v})&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Linear maps are the structure-preserving maps (&lt;a href="../../../objects/prealgebra/terms/homomorphism.md" class="link-internal"&gt;homomorphisms&lt;/a&gt;) of vector spaces. The kernel &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;ker&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;{&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∣&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn mathvariant="bold"&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;}&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\ker(T) = \{\mathbf{v} \mid T(\mathbf{v}) = \mathbf{0}\}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and image &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;im&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;{&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∣&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∈&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;}&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\operatorname{im}(T) = \{T(\mathbf{v}) \mid \mathbf{v} \in V\}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; are subspaces, and the rank-nullity theorem states &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;dim&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;dim&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;ker&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;dim&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;im&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⁡&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\dim V = \dim \ker(T) + \dim \operatorname{im}(T)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href="../../../objects/categories/index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;category theory&lt;/a&gt;, linear maps are the &lt;a href="../../../objects/categories/ordinary-categories/terms/morphism.md" class="link-internal"&gt;morphisms&lt;/a&gt; in the category of vector spaces over a field.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Matrix</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/matrix/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/matrix/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A matrix is a rectangular array of scalars from a &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/field.md" class="link-internal"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;F&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, arranged in rows and columns. An &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;m&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;×&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;m \times n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; matrix has &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;m&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;m&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; rows and &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; columns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every &lt;a href="./linear-map.md" class="link-internal"&gt;linear map&lt;/a&gt; between finite-dimensional &lt;a href="./vector-space.md" class="link-internal"&gt;vector spaces&lt;/a&gt; can be represented by a matrix, once bases are chosen. Matrix multiplication corresponds to &lt;a href="../../../objects/categories/ordinary-categories/terms/composition.md" class="link-internal"&gt;composition&lt;/a&gt; of linear maps. The set of &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;×&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;n \times n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; matrices over &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;F&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; forms a (generally non-commutative) &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/ring.md" class="link-internal"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A square matrix is invertible if and only if its &lt;a href="./determinant.md" class="link-internal"&gt;determinant&lt;/a&gt; is nonzero, equivalently if the corresponding linear map is bijective.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Vector</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/vector/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/vector/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A vector is an element of a &lt;a href="./vector-space.md" class="link-internal"&gt;vector space&lt;/a&gt;. In &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="double-struck"&gt;R&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\mathbb{R}^n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, a vector is an ordered &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;-tuple of real numbers such as &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;3&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo separator="true"&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;−&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo separator="true"&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;4&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;(3, -1, 4)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. But vectors need not be tuples of numbers — &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/polynomial.md" class="link-internal"&gt;polynomials&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="../../../concepts/function/index.md" class="link-internal"&gt;functions&lt;/a&gt;, and many other objects can be vectors, provided their containing set satisfies the vector space axioms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A vector is characterized not by what it &amp;ldquo;is&amp;rdquo; but by what operations it supports: it can be added to other vectors and scaled by elements of the underlying &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/field.md" class="link-internal"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Vector Space</title><link>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/vector-space/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://emsenn.net/library/math/domains/linear-algebra/terms/vector-space/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A vector space over a &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/field.md" class="link-internal"&gt;field&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;F&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a set &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;V&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; with an addition making &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator="true"&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;+&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo separator="true"&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn mathvariant="bold"&gt;0&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo stretchy="false"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;(V, +, \mathbf{0})&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; an &lt;a href="../../../objects/groups/terms/abelian-group.md" class="link-internal"&gt;abelian group&lt;/a&gt;, together with a scalar multiplication &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;×&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;→&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;F \times V \to V&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; satisfying compatibility, distributivity, and &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⋅&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="bold"&gt;v&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;1 \cdot \mathbf{v} = \mathbf{v}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A vector space is determined up to &lt;a href="../../../objects/categories/ordinary-categories/terms/isomorphism.md" class="link-internal"&gt;isomorphism&lt;/a&gt; by its &lt;a href="./dimension.md" class="link-internal"&gt;dimension&lt;/a&gt; — the cardinality of any &lt;a href="./basis.md" class="link-internal"&gt;basis&lt;/a&gt;. Two finite-dimensional vector spaces over the same field are isomorphic if and only if they have the same dimension.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When the scalars come from a &lt;a href="../../algebra/terms/ring.md" class="link-internal"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; rather than a field, the structure is called a &lt;strong&gt;module&lt;/strong&gt;. Modules are more general and less well-behaved than vector spaces.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>